### Analysis of the Main Target Image:

- **Count & Layers:** The structure consists of 12 building blocks arranged in multiple layers. There are two main structures: one on the left and one on the right.
  - The left structure has a base layer with two red arches (blocks), followed by a middle layer with two yellow half-cylinders, and a top layer with two green rectangular blocks and two yellow rectangular blocks.
  - The right structure has a base layer with one red arch, a middle layer with one green rectangular block, and a top layer with one blue rectangular block topped by an orange triangular roof.

- **Spatial Relationships:**
  - The two red arches on the left are adjacent to each other.
  - The two yellow half-cylinders sit on top of the red arches.
  - The two green rectangular blocks and two yellow rectangular blocks are placed above the yellow half-cylinders.
  - The red arch on the right supports the green rectangular block.
  - The blue rectangular block is placed on top of the green rectangular block.
  - The orange triangular roof sits on top of the blue rectangular block.

### Selection of Required Blocks from the Dictionary:

- **Block Indices:**
  - Red Arch: Index 1
  - Yellow Half-Cylinder: Index 13
  - Green Rectangular Block: Index 6
  - Yellow Rectangular Block: Index 10
  - Blue Rectangular Block: Index 3
  - Orange Triangular Roof: Index 15
